Description: Godin's A6 Ultra Baritone provides players with booming sound, a smooth-playing neck, and high-quality electronics. This guitar's chambered silver leaf maple body virtually eliminates feedback while keeping resonance and projection very much alive, with the entire baritone range at your disposal. The maple neck's 16" fingerboard radius and 1.8" nut width make it easy to play, while a Godin GJN1 Mini Humbucker allows for easy use in a live setting or for recording, all while preserving the guitar's stellar sound. If you're looking for a high-quality baritone acoustic-electric, then look no further than the Godin A6 Ultra Baritone.Specs:-Chamber Silver Leaf Maple body-Solid Cedar Top-Maple neck-Richlite Fingerboard-16" (406 mm) fingerboard radius-27" (686 mm) Scale-1.8" nut width-Godin GJN1 Mini-Humbucker -Custom Godin under Saddle Transducer and custom preamp with Volume, Mid, Treble and Bass controls as well as independent volume, treble and bass controls for the Humbucker.-2 output jacks: electric & acoustic mix -Semi-gloss Burst FinishThis guitar has barely been used; there is no fret wear; it is indistinguishable from new other than the 1 flaw I could find, a small ding on the surface which is only noticeable when reflected off the light, thanks to the dark sunburst satin finish (see images).
